  • Exact and approximate results

By default, Mathematica outputs the exact result as 2^100 = 1267650600228229401496703205376 rather than 1.26765*10^30. To output the approximate results, the input should become 2^100//N (N ‚Äì numerical).

When the input has an explicit decimal point, the corresponding output becomes an approximate result.
